	   <tr><td colspan=2>I used a flawless horn as well trying to get my wind skill to go up for several days and not so much as 1 point from it. I think it's a bug because when I switched over to a store bought flute, my skill went up very fast. Now if I could just get brass to rise up as quickly.<br><br>By the way, Cinda's Charismatic Carillon song is a wind song, just target an npc and let it play. That's a lvl 11 song or if you're 19 and have Shauri's Sonorous Clouding (invis), that is also a wind song and you don't need to target anything.<br><br>FYI: for those wanting to practice brass instrument skill but don't want to make any nearby npc's mad at you, there is a spot in north karana that I use. It's perfect if you have the singing steel gaunts for the enduring breath effect and you can increase your swimming skill while practicing brass. Just come off the wooden bridge and turn right following the shoreline. Go into the water and swim to the middle of the river where you will hit the zone line. Hit num lock on your keypad to auto-swim then equip your brass instrument, start playing Denon's Disruptive Discord (lvl 18) and you're skill in brass and swimming will rise. Don't worry about the one guard in the general area, he is well out of range of the song and he doesn't wander. And there are no mobs that wander by either. You don't need a target for the song, if it's grayed out, it's playing.<br><br>Also if you don't have singing steel guants and don't want to sit there twisting eb song, just tap your 9 key on your number pad until you are swimming above the surface of the water. Your bard will stick itself into the groove at the zone line and stay there.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Aug&nbsp;&nbsp;8 16:54:26 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
