	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 4th 10:56 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.58]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think one of the nicest zones for new bards, once you get to level 13, is Unrest.&nbsp;&nbsp;Great exp, and the loot is good.  Not many people there at all, either.  You can solo the beetles for two levels and then start on the others.  Getting a group is even sweeter, but hard to do there sometimes.<br><br>A real nice side effect (and I have noticed this twice while taking new characters there) is that in unrest a lot of stuff drops (like ringmail, thick leather apron, etc.) that is useful for new people, but experienced people will often just give away because it is heavy or only good for lowbies.  Just thank them, turn on the Selo's, and go sell it if you don't need it to wear.  <br><br>Until level 13, fighting in CB and selling the belts is the best way to gain level and get money.<br><br>Yes, there are trains both places.  So?  You will still level faster in these two dungeons than just about anywhere else.  Hey, if you want to be a hero you aren't going to live forever. (smile)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
